text.section:
An agreement by an owner, the primary purpose of which is to locate, deliver, recover, or assist in the recovery of property and that is not in violation of subsection (1) of this section, is enforceable only if:
The agreement is in writing;
The agreement provides that the fee or compensation agreed upon is an amount not more than ten percent (10%) of the value of the property collected;
The agreement clearly sets forth the nature of the property and the services to be rendered;
The agreement is signed by the apparent owner; and
The agreement states the value of the property before and after the fee or other compensation has been deducted.
